<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,946,2012]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,946,972]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Characters that differentiate 
<taxonomicName authority="Fernández-Triana &amp; Ravelo, 2007" authorityName="Fernández-Triana &amp; Ravelo" authorityYear="2007" box="[624,767,946,971]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Eiphosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dearmasi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[624,767,946,971]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">E. dearmasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[775,870,946,972]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[775,870,946,972]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
from all species other than those of its speciesgroup are presented in the diagnosis for 
<emphasis box="[620,740,986,1011]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Alayo" baseAuthorityYear="1973" box="[620,736,986,1011]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Eiphosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luteum">E. luteum</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
In 
<collectingCountry box="[779,841,986,1012]" name="Cuba" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Cuba</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName authority="Fernández-Triana &amp; Ravelo, 2007" authorityName="Fernández-Triana &amp; Ravelo" authorityYear="2007" box="[848,989,986,1011]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Eiphosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dearmasi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[848,989,986,1011]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">E. dearmasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[996,1090,986,1012]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[996,1090,986,1012]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cresson" authorityYear="1865" box="[151,344,1026,1051]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Eiphosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrovittatum">
<emphasis box="[151,344,1026,1051]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">E. nigrovittatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from that species in having a much more yellowish metatibia, the mesopleuron completely yellow (with diagonal black stripe in 
<emphasis box="[726,893,1066,1091]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">nigrovittattum</emphasis>
), and a shorter ovipositor.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,946,2012]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,352,1106,1132]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Description:</emphasis>
Forewing length 7.00 mm. Mandible strongly tapered towards distal end, with upper tooth slightly longer and stouter than lower one; clypeus, in profile, convex, malar space 0.55X as long as basal mandibular width; posterior ocellus separated from eye by 0.95X its own maximum diameter. Pronotum with dorsal end of epomia raised forming rounded flange laterally; mesoscutum abruptely rounded, coarsely punctured, with lateral lobes more sparsely punctate; scutellum weakly convex, smooth centrally; mesopleuron with ventral part punctate; sternaulus sharply impressed anteriorly; dorsal end of epicnemial carina extending to anterior end of pleuron about half way up pronotum; metapleuron convex and smooth; submetapleural carina moderately long and elevated. Propodeum very sparsely punctate and impressed centrally; anterior transverse carina complete, with median angulation strong; posterior transverse carina incomplete. Profemur with long but sparse pubescence ventrally, longest seta about half diameter of femur; metathoracic leg with trochantellus, in dorsal view, 0.63X as long as trochanter; metafemur 5.90X as long as deep, metatibia spinose, metatarsal claw lacking in 
<typeStatus box="[471,577,1546,1572]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">holotype</typeStatus>
. Forewing 
<emphasis box="[711,779,1547,1572]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">3rs-m</emphasis>
absent; 
<emphasis box="[880,949,1547,1572]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">2rm-s</emphasis>
about 0.50X length of 
<emphasis box="[1228,1252,1547,1572]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">M</emphasis>
between 
<emphasis box="[1367,1436,1547,1572]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">2rm-s</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[200,273,1587,1612]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">2m-cu</emphasis>
; distal abscissa of 
<emphasis box="[494,518,1587,1612]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">M</emphasis>
pigmented its entire length; 
<emphasis box="[853,905,1587,1612]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">cu-a</emphasis>
opposite to base of 
<emphasis box="[1140,1216,1587,1612]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Rs&amp;M</emphasis>
. Hind wing with 4 hamuli. Metasoma tergite I slightly swollen posteriorly, with spiracle positioned 0.70 of way back; tergite II dorsally with fine and sparse setae in apical half. Ovipositor straight, 1.53X as long as metatibia; ovipositor sheath with long and dense pubescence.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,946,2012]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,290,1746,1772]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Colour.</emphasis>
Head yellow with frons centrally, part of occiput and dorsal part of gena black; mesosoma mainly yellow but mesoscutum black with yellow marks anterolaterally, meeting posteriorly; metanotum and median longitudinal stripe on propodeum black. Metasoma orange-brown, with black basal spot in tergite II. Prothoracic leg yellowish; posterior legs orange-brown, with tibia apically and basally brownish and with yellow central band; metatarsus lacking in 
<typeStatus box="[612,718,1906,1932]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">holotype</typeStatus>
. Wings hyaline with apical third of forewing infumate; pterostigma brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="6" pageNumber="55" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,946,2012]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1435,152,258]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,339,1986,2012]" pageId="6" pageNumber="55">Etymology.</emphasis>
We dedicate this species to our friend and colleague Luis F. De Armas (IES) as a gesture of thanks for his tireless efforts collecting and studying Cuban arthropods.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
